Experiment-3¶

Aim:¶

  1. Record a speech file of 2 sec with sampling frequency of 8kHz and plot it.

  2. Frame the recorded speech with frame length of 20 ms with overlap an overlap of 25%. Calculate the frame length and the number of frames.

  3. Applying Hamming window on speech frames and analyse the frames.

  4. Calculate ZCR and STE of each frame of the speech file.

In [16]:
fl_ms = 20
ov_per = 25
FL = float(fl_ms)*10**-3*fs
OV = float(ov_per)*FL/100
FS=  FL-OV

rms = librosa.feature.rms(ss,frame_length=int(FL),hop_length=int(FS))
rms = rms[0]
rms = librosa.util.normalize(rms,axis=0)


zcr = librosa.feature.zero_crossing_rate(ss,frame_length=int(FL),hop_length=int(FS),threshold=0)
zcr = zcr[0]
